The Gauteng Education Department says some township schools will now be open on weekends to assist the parents who want to apply for the 2018 academic year. JOHANNESBURG The Gauteng Education Department says some township schools will now be open on weekends to assist the parents of grade 1 and 8 pupils who want to apply for the 2018 academic year.This weekend the department visited several schools in Soweto and Mohlakeng.Online registration commenced earlier this month and will close on 12 June.The department says it has received over 300,000 applications so far.The department's Steve Mabona said, In some areas, the numbers aren t good so we decided to go to different townships on weekends. 